  "steps": [
    {
      "title": "Breaking down the plywood",
      "body": "Start by breaking down the plywood using a circular saw and the rip cut and accu-cut saw guides.\nDownloadable plans and templates can be found in the \"Extras\" tab.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/4245fe336874883e.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Adhering the Templates",
      "body": "Some of the boards cut from the plywood are going to trimmed up into pieces for parts used to makes the sides. The templates are provide in the plans (https://rogueengineer.com/diy-1-sheet-plywood-chair-set-plans/) and should be adhered to the appropriate boards using spray adhesive.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/429c69d94748faba.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Cutting out the Parts",
      "body": "With the templates adhered, I used the accu-cut, supporting the track on both ends to cut out all the parts.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/646876c49dc7dde7.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Aligning the sides",
      "body": "Gather all the parts and align the sides using a straight edge to keep the feet flat. Make sure the half lap joint is nice and tight.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/3581a226b914d642.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Assembling the Legs",
      "body": "Lift up the parts on top and then adhere them into place with wood glue.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/caaa1bc27a0cee96.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Assembling the Sides",
      "body": "Glue and nail the half lap joint together. Then fill and sand the seams flush.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/84369d74e3b23853.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Install Back Support",
      "body": "Drill pocket holes and install the back support to the sides using 1-1/4\" pocket screws.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/cf2e074fc6163eaf.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Install the Seat",
      "body": "Set the seat in place and mark the pocket hole locations. Drill the pocket holes and install the seat using 1-1/4\" pocket screws.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/3a12891d3ca17e61.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Install the Back",
      "body": "I slid the back in from the top of the chair and squirted some glue in the gap then clamped the back in place until the glue cured.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/ab0be21fc1d8a6e2.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Assembling the Table Base",
      "body": "Assemble the table base using wood glue and 1-1/2\" brad nails.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/6eca259f7f5dd57c.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Assemble the Side Table",
      "body": "Install the base to the table top using wood glue and 1-1/4\" brad nails.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/22013badc18307cc.webp"
    }
  ],
